n="22" break="no"/><supplied reason="lost">le prabu</supplied>ddha-kumudāgara-śuddha-tāre||</l><!--
L22. F translates kumudāgara as "a bed of waterlilies". Sircar (plausibly) thinks Fleet took āgara as equivalent to āgāra (which is legit); he, instead, says it means amāvasyā. But this too is problematic, since the day is śukla trayodaśī, which is (on or around) the full moon day.
--></lg>
